Experience
I am Software Developer





I am an experienced IT professional with a strong background in software and web development. Over the course of my 3-year career, I have honed my skills in technologies such as Node.js, TypeScript, React.js, JavaScript, Java, Python, and Microsoft Bot Framework v3. I have a proven track record in developing web applications using various front-end technologies, including CSS, HTML, and Bootstrap, as well as expertise in back-end development using a range of databases such as MySQL, Microsoft SQL Server, and MongoDB. My experience also extends to implementing continuous integration and deployment (CI/CD) using tools like Jenkins, Docker, and Ansible, demonstrating a commitment to optimizing software development processes.




My technical skills encompass a wide array of programming languages, including Node.js, JavaScript, TypeScript, and C++, among others. I am well-versed in working with markup languages like HTML and CSS, as well as various database systems such as MongoDB, MySQL, and PostgreSQL. With experience in multiple operating systems, including Linux and Windows, and proficiency in cloud technologies like Azure, I possess a versatile skill set.




In addition to my technical abilities, I hold a Master of Applied Computing with a CGPA of 3.7/4 and a Bachelor's degree in Computer Science and Engineering. I have worked as a Software Developer Intern at BlackBerry and as a Software Developer at Tata Consultancy Services, where I contributed to projects involving TypeScript, PHP, React.js, Python, and more. My experience is marked by a commitment to delivering efficient, reliable, and scalable solutions while collaborating effectively with cross-functional teams and clients. My dedication to continuous learning is reflected in my AZ-204 Developing Solutions for Microsoft Azure certification.
